at|
barnets: Welcome to everybody. Thank you to Maureen Hall for inviting me to do this lecture. Also thanks to Miksa and Peterb370 at BIL for coaching me in bridge movies and how to show them.

OK let's go everybody - fasten your seatbelts!

As it is my first presentation I want you all to enjoy it. Therefore while there are some important ideas on teaching  there is also a strong accent on entertainment. I have been working on some new presentation ideas which combine some learning ideas with entertainment for the student.
|
pg| ***** 2 ***** |


at|
A few hands shown are from "Put yourself in the Hot Seat" a lecture I am currently giving allowing the student the chance to find the winning play at the critical point in the hand. I feature the hands and stories on a full size cinema type screen and there are pictures of the players in their seat positions. If you like what you see here send me an email BridgeIdeas@@aol.com and you can get on my mailing list to see more presentations and also free access to my first Website, Shenkinbridge which will be up  shortly. Constructive comments are also welcome sent as an email.

I now live in USA but originally from Glasgow, Scotland.
This is my first presentation on BBO so I ask you to put up with occasional blips that are likely to occur.
|
pg| ***** 3 ***** |


at|
Today the main focus is on opening leads.

A bridge teaching book will tell which card you should lead from various holdings on opening lead. I like to help student's think perhaps in a different way from the way they normally do.

So today I would like you to give yourself an idea of what the four hands round the table look like before you lead. This different type of approach may be difficult to grasp at first but if you can make a start today you will reap the benefits in the future.|
pg| ***** 4 ***** |


