Q: When does a double indicate to lead first bid suit, please?
barnets: The opening leader leans towards dummy's first suit. The Dbl asks partner not to make his normal lead, so it steers him towards dummy's first suit or a long suit which would not be construed as the normal lead. Sometimes even experts get it wrong, but better to have it than nothing.|
